If `f : M‚ÇÅ ‚Üí‚Çó[A] M‚ÇÇ` is a linear map between modules, `pres‚ÇÇ` is a presentation of `M‚ÇÇ` and `g‚ÇÅ : Œπ ‚Üí M‚ÇÅ` is a family of generators of `M‚ÇÅ` (which is expressed as `hg‚ÇÅ : Submodule.span A (Set.range g‚ÇÅ) = ‚ä§`), then we provide a way to obtain a presentation of the cokernel of `f`. It requires an additional data `data : pres‚ÇÇ.CokernelData f g‚ÇÅ`, which consists of liftings of the images by `f` of the generators of `M‚ÇÅ` as linear combinations of the generators of `M‚ÇÇ`. Then, we obtain a presentation `pres‚ÇÇ.cokernel data hg‚ÇÅ : Presentation A (M‚ÇÇ ‚ß∏ LinearMap.range f)`.

---
